			<div class="content" id="post-content-4161008">
									

<p>Salutations everyone! SoullessSingularity is looking for members interested in joining the Site Crit team as Junior Staff.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Crit things posted on the site. There will be a minimum of 3 crits per week, preferably more if you can handle the workload.</li>
<li>Join our crit IRC channel, #thecritters on Synirc, and attend monthly googledoc meetings over a weekend</li>
<li>Report to me every other week to let me know how you've been keeping up with the work. It's okay if you were busy for a week or so.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What You Get In Return:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>After ~2-3 months on the team, <em>I am able to nominate you for promotion to fully Operational Staff</em> (which occurs every 4 months). (Note: If I choose not to nominate you, and you're curious why, I will be completely open with you about it.)</li>
<li>An experience of staff ongoings, such as policy discussion and other staff shenaningans.</li>
<li>The ability to post to the staff site. You won't be responsible for voting or anything but can give your view on policies relevant to site crit.</li>
<li>Junior staff posts, a say in crit policy</li>
<li>The opportunity to PM me a crit of yours once a week to get tips and tricks!</li>
<li>No pressure- if it's not for you, there's nothing forcing you to keep at it.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>If you're interested, please post on this thread with the following information, and if I don't respond, reach out to me in IRC:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Site Crit team?</p>
<p>How active are you?</p>
<p>How much experience do you have with critting in general- have you attended any workshops or classes IRL?</p>
<p>Can you link me to a recent critique you've done? Please not your best work, just what you'd normally do on the team. (Note: I'm not looking necessarily for long or thorough. Insight and the ability to point the big flaws in a quick manner is also useful.)</p>
</blockquote>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Living the dream, or dreaming the life?</p>

