			<div class="content" id="post-content-4478407">
									

<p>Hey, name's Cyvstvi!</p>
<p>1Q. Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Site Crit team?</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+1A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-1A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>1A. I've always wanted to be part of the site ever since I was, what, thirteen when I first heard about SCPs in general. Since then, I decided to join the site fully this year and in the process have learnt a lot about the way the site functions and runs. I think I'd be an excellent addition to Junior Staff since I'm a friendly face that's always willing to equally help the newer, and advanced folks out. I want to be part of a community that has a bunch of passionate people all geared towards writing fiction about a dystopian world where anomalous entities are all the norm for those people. It's fun.</p>
<p>As for why I'd like to join the Site Crit team, I feel I would be a valuable asset as my skills in both creative writing, the English language and writing essay style answers with a clinical and formal tone are all useful skills for critiquing others work. To end, I'd like to be able to work alongside like-minded individuals and help myself, and them work towards a common goal of more successful tales, articles, and more.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
2Q. How active are you?
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+2A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-2A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>2A. I'm fairly active, usually browsing the IRC and Critique Forums as well as newly added articles, always willing to voice an opinion and assist others with their creative writing.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
3Q. How much experience do you have with critting in general- have you attended any workshops or classes IRL?
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+3A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-3A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>3A. I have a large amount of experience critting both creative, and formal writing. For example, I used to attend creative writing classes at sixth-form and thoroughly enjoyed those classes. At university, I have applied myself towards critique more leaned towards academia such as historical and political essays that engage in thematic discussion whilst also being a member of the debating society so I am able to better express my opinions and critique in a more neutral and conciliatory manner. I have done some critting on this website and in the IRC.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
4Q. Can you link me to a recent critique you've done? Please not your best work, just what you'd normally do on the team. (Note: I'm not looking necessarily for long or thorough. Insight and the ability to point the big flaws in a quick manner is also useful.)
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+4A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-4A</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>4A. Here was my last critique that I issued - <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-12967804/a-chat-with-everyone">http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-12967804/a-chat-with-everyone</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
Thank you in advance for taking the time to look through, any feedback you give would be amazing and you can contact me through Wikidot PMs or through IRC, thank you once again.
							</div>

								
