			<div class="content" id="post-content-4197253">
									

<p><strong>Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Site Crit team?</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I believe that I have demonstrated through my (now four months long!) commitment to the Forum Criticism team that I am both capable and willing to read through and offer my insight to works on the wiki. I'm also a frequent contributor to the wiki, so I have a finger to the pulse of current expectations and standards.</p>
<p>It is for these reasons that I think I would be a good fit to Site Crit. It'll force me into a position to offer my knowledge to the community at large.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>How active are you?</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I visit the site routinely six days a week (I try to be away on Sundays, because otherwise I will never get time to myself otherwise). I'm typically the most active in the afternoon and late evenings. I'm on IRC frequently.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>How much experience do you have with critting in general- have you attended any workshops or classes IRL?</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I've attended most of the crit seminars run by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/taylor-itkin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3208919); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3208919&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1553586222" alt="taylor_itkin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3208919)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/taylor-itkin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3208919); return false;">taylor_itkin</a></span>. I've also been an active member of Forum Crit since December 2018.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Can you link me to a recent critique you've done? Please not your best work, just what you'd normally do on the team. (Note: I'm not looking necessarily for long or thorough. Insight and the ability to point the big flaws in a quick manner is also useful.)</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Here is <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-10759186/the-computer-chip-zombie-thing#post-4194896">one idea</a> and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-10668377/new-scp-draft:how-to-speak-good-english#post-4191686">one draft</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

