<p>Ayy I didn’t know this existed.</p>
<p>“Why do you feel you should be a junior staff? Why the Site Crit team?”</p>
<p>I was on forum criticism before retiring conscientiously. I’m back now kinda, and doing my best to work like I used to. If you’ve seen any of my work from forum crit, you’ll know that my critiques are ludicrously in-depth, often going through every single line of an article multiple times before publishing the critique an hour later. On Site Crit, I believe I’ll be capable of delivering smaller, but impactful critique that’ll be good for authors and also good for my head.</p>
<p>“How active are you?“</p>
<p>I’m on every day in some capacity. Certainly enough to write critique for completed works.</p>
<p>&quot;How much experience do you have with critting in general- have you attended any workshops or classes IRL?&quot;</p>
<p>Reviewed the script work of others while working on my own script for High School ‘sketch fest.’ Routine beginner critique experience during high school creative writing and mandated nanowrimo project. Even more extensive critique experience in 2 semesters of progressively advanced fiction writing courses (where I routinely draw the ‘I once reviewed a draft that purposefully had no capital letters’ story from) at the University of Virginia. Anything else comes from hobbyist reading/writing on my own time.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-11126830/ghost">old crit</a></p>

